> Should we fold this into the DockerClient to avoid needing to pass around the flag

In this case the Invoker could optimistically try to use `runc` and, in case of error, fallback on `docker`, and save this information next time it needs to `pause`/`resume` a container. `pause`/`resume` would only work when the binary inside the Invoker container is compatible with `runc` on the host, otherwise we're getting: ```stderr: json: cannot unmarshal object into Go value of type []string``` . #2799 solves this error by mounting `runc` from the host, but it only works if `runc` doesn't have other dependent libraries.

@dgrove-oss in the current kube deploy that you're testing with, I assume the binary on the host is compatible with the binary in the invoker and you didn't get the `unmarshall` error ?
